article.description: Adam Koch scored 14 points and Northern Iowa defeated Drake 67-51 Wednesday night.
article.headline: Northern Iowa's tough defense stifles Drake
article.linkText: No. 25 N. Iowa ends Drake's 5-game win streak

inlines.body:
Fast Facts

• Northern Iowa defended its home court against Drake for the first time since Jan. 21, 2006 (had lost three straight home games to Drake).

• The loss snapped Drake's five-game win streak.

• Drake scored fewer than 50 points for the third time this season, all of which have happened since the New Year.

-- ESPN Stats & Information

article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa -- Adam Koch scored 14 points and Northern Iowa (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today) defeated Drake 67-51 Wednesday night. The Panthers (18-2, 9-1 Missouri Valley) beat their third Division I team from Iowa this season. Northern Iowa already owned victories over Iowa and Iowa State. Jordan Eglseder and Ali Farokhmanesh scored 10 points apiece for the conference-leading Panthers, now 9-0 at the McLeod Center this season. Northern Iowa, which ranked second in the country in scoring defense entering Wednesday at 55.4 points per game, played more good defense to snap Drake's five-game winning streak. The Bulldogs (10-12, 5-5) had been the hottest team in the Missouri Valley before running into the stingy Panthers. Josh Young led Drake with 12 points and Adam Templeton scored 10.
